2. Look for Durability and Coverage
Not all paints are created equal. Some brands offer superior durability and coverage, which means youâ€™ll need fewer coats to achieve a professional finish. Higher-quality paints tend to be more resistant to fading, peeling, and stains.
ğŸ“Œ Key Features to Look For:
One-coat coverage: Some premium paints require fewer coats, saving you time and money.
Scrubbable finish: If you have kids or pets, opt for a paint that can withstand cleaning.
Fade resistance: Choose a brand that retains its color over time, especially for exterior projects.
Brands like Benjamin Moore, Sherwin-Williams, and Behr are known for their superior coverage and durability.

3. Choose the Right Finish
Paint comes in various finishes, from flat to high-gloss. The brand you choose should offer a variety of finishes to suit different rooms in your home.
ğŸ¨ Common Paint Finishes:
Flat/Matte: Best for ceilings and low-traffic areas. It hides imperfections but is harder to clean.
Eggshell/Satin: Ideal for living rooms, bedrooms, and hallways. It has a slight sheen and is easier to clean.
Semi-Gloss: Perfect for kitchens and bathrooms due to its moisture resistance and easy-to-clean surface.
High-Gloss: Great for doors, trim, and cabinets, providing a shiny, durable finish.
Popular brands like Valspar and PPG offer a wide range of finishes to match your needs.

